WEBVTT

00:00:01.459 --> 00:00:08.900
Welcome. We're going to discuss the importance of setting personal goals in the ministry.

00:00:08.900 --> 00:00:12.660
But first, here are some updates.

00:00:12.660 --> 00:00:21.780
On January 1st of this year, a magnitude 7.6 earthquake struck central Japan. Thankfully,

00:00:21.780 --> 00:00:30.500
none of our brothers were killed. But over 100 of their homes were damaged, and two

00:00:30.500 --> 00:00:40.179
were destroyed. Also, nine kingdom halls were damaged. The branch office quickly provided

00:00:40.179 --> 00:00:46.100
accommodations and other necessities for our brothers and sisters. Soon after, the branch

00:00:46.100 --> 00:00:52.340
appointed a disaster relief committee, and sent branch representatives to visit our brothers

00:00:52.340 --> 00:00:59.140
in the affected areas. Within just a few days, additional relief aid was delivered to congregations

00:00:59.140 --> 00:01:05.459
in need. In the Wajima congregation, the elders couldn't account for one sister.

00:01:06.180 --> 00:01:11.939
To reach her, an elder walked for eight hours avoiding landslides and cracks in the ground,

00:01:12.500 --> 00:01:15.459
until he was able to confirm that she was safe.

00:01:17.219 --> 00:01:22.739
Congregations in the area, including those severely affected, have held their meetings from

00:01:22.739 --> 00:01:28.260
the very weak the earthquake yet. Most of the publishers have gathered in person

00:01:28.260 --> 00:01:35.299
to encourage one another. We're praying for our brothers and sisters in Japan and in other lands

00:01:35.299 --> 00:01:43.780
affected by recent disasters. On January 1st, the Patterson Visitor Center officially opened for

00:01:43.780 --> 00:01:50.819
tours. Construction began in early 2021 and was completed in September 2023.

00:01:52.019 --> 00:01:56.019
What will you experience when you come for a visit? Let's take a look.

00:02:04.379 --> 00:02:08.620
The Patterson Visitor Center features three museums and a coin display.

00:02:12.259 --> 00:02:17.300
The first exhibit you'll notice is entitled Defending and Legally Establishing the Good News.

00:02:18.259 --> 00:02:23.060
It presents the powerful experiences of men, women, and even schoolchildren

00:02:23.060 --> 00:02:26.419
who held to their Bible-based beliefs despite legal opposition.

00:02:27.139 --> 00:02:31.699
This exhibit shows how Jehovah's Organization supported them through difficult tests.

00:02:31.699 --> 00:02:38.979
A Biblical coin gallery presents a unique display of original coins that were in circulation

00:02:38.979 --> 00:02:43.300
in the first century, along with their scriptural context and significance.

00:02:44.740 --> 00:02:50.659
Another exhibit, entitled All Your Sons Will Be Taught by Jehovah, features some of the training

00:02:50.659 --> 00:02:55.699
programs and schools that have been used by Jehovah's Modern Day Organization to equip us as

00:02:55.699 --> 00:03:02.259
ministers and teachers. We trust it will motivate you to see additional ways that you can take

00:03:02.259 --> 00:03:09.139
advantage of the education Jehovah provides. Our feature museum is a first-century Bible village.

00:03:10.819 --> 00:03:15.539
The local villagers are very welcoming and will be eager to show you how they live and work

00:03:15.539 --> 00:03:21.780
together as a community. You'll see firsthand what life was like when Jesus walked the Earth.

00:03:22.659 --> 00:03:29.139
You'll walk through agricultural areas, a marketplace, residences, a synagogue,

00:03:29.939 --> 00:03:37.139
and even by the seashore. No doubt these new museums will enhance your appreciation for the

00:03:37.139 --> 00:03:45.169
Bible and for what Jehovah is accomplishing through his organization today. We welcome all who are

00:03:45.169 --> 00:03:57.460
able to come and see the New Patterson Visitor Center. The Patterson Visitor Center is

00:03:57.460 --> 00:04:04.659
outstanding. We thank all who worked on this project and we now invite all of you to come and tour.

00:04:05.379 --> 00:04:13.939
You can request a tour on www.org. Now, let's talk about the recent adjustments to the way we

00:04:13.939 --> 00:04:20.259
report our ministry and how these affect our personal goals. At the recent annual meeting,

00:04:20.899 --> 00:04:26.339
we learned that as of last November, we had no longer be submitting a detailed field service

00:04:26.339 --> 00:04:34.180
report. That was a big change, wasn't it? But although we've changed the way we report our activity,

00:04:34.180 --> 00:04:42.660
we haven't changed the way we view the ministry itself. The focus is on people. We love people,

00:04:42.660 --> 00:04:47.379
and we want to help them. We're ready to share the good news wherever we find them.

00:04:48.420 --> 00:04:54.980
